OL,5, Average pay growth rose above inflation
OL,6, for the first time in almost two years,
OL,7, in a sign that the squeeze on living   
OL,8, costs may be starting to ease.         
OL,10,FWages rose by 7.8% between June and    
OL,11,FAugust, according to official figures. 
OL,13,FIt is higher than average inflation    
OL,14,Fover the same three months, which      
OL,15,Fmeasures the rate at which prices rise.
OL,17,FThe last time that pay growth overtook 
OL,18,Fprice increases was in October 2021,   
OL,19,Fwhich was during the Covid pandemic.   
